# chunk: split a flat byte string into fixed 4-byte records (a Stride(4) inner list — the surface
# producer of wide strides), then sort them. The sort takes the stride fast path (each 4-byte record
# packs to a u64 key). "dcba","ABCD" sort to "ABCD","dcba" — uppercase precedes lowercase in ASCII.
# n = 1
# = Sum tags=[0] [List ends=[2] <List ends=[4, 8] <[65, 66, 67, 68, 100, 99, 98, 97]>>, ()x0]
input "dcbaABCD" chunk 4 sort
